{
  "texts": [
    "First, the frequencies of all words in the MWOs are recorded.",
    "TF-IDF then incorporates a concept called inverse document frequency (Sparck Jones, 1972).",
    "This measures the amount of information provided by a word by looking at how frequently it is present in the corpus.",
    "We use the Scikit-learn library's (Pedregosa et al., 2011) TF-IDF implementation in Python.",
    "TF-IDF is defined as the product of t f (t, D) (TF or term-frequency) and id f (t, D) 123 Fig. 5 Keyword based matching (IDF or inverse document frequency) where TF is the number of times a word or term appears in the total number of documents, and IDF computes how uncommon or rare a term is across all documents."
  ]
}